      "message": "Those are explicitly different: the repository is considered consistent as soon as the underlying Git repository exists and is recognised as such, so that it can be reindexed.\n\nA different argument is that the `isUpToDate` implementation is incomplete, because it should also check that the meta-ref on the repository (refs/meta/config) corresponds to the SHA1 in the `ProjectIndexEvent`.\n\nThe problem is that `ProjectIndexEvent` doesn\u0027t include the SHA1 yet, so a complete up-to-date check isn\u0027t possible.",
